    "body": "# Background\r\nWhen running `pytest` using `python3.8` on `MacOS` exceptions of the following kind are raised:\r\n```\r\nFAILED tests/test_database/test_mining_cache.py::TestCreateMiningCache:: ...\r\nAttributeError: Can't pickle local object ...\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe prototypical code that raises such exceptions is:\r\n```python\r\nimport multiprocessing as mp\r\n\r\n\r\nclass TestSomething:\r\n    def test_error(self):\r\n        def worker():\r\n            pass\r\n\r\n        proc = mp.Process(target=worker)\r\n        proc.start()\r\n        proc.join()\r\n```\r\n\r\n# Solution\r\nAs explained in [this answer](https://stackoverflow.com/a/52283968/2804645) the reason for the exception is:\r\n- In order to be sent to a new process the local function `worker` needs to be pickled\r\n- Pickling actually only saves the function name, and upon unpickling the function is re-imported by that name\r\n- Since the function is local it cannot be imported by the name\r\n\r\nSo in order to avoid this error it's sufficient to move the local function to a scope from which it can be imported by name. We move it to a static method of the test class:\r\n```python\r\nclass TestSomething:\r\n    @staticmethod\r\n    def worker():\r\n        pass\r\n\r\n    def test_error(self):\r\n        proc = mp.Process(target=self.worker)\r\n        proc.start()\r\n        proc.join()\r\n```\r\n\r\n# P.S.\r\n- I have no idea why this error only occurs in `python3.8` on `MacOS`.\r\n- I made a small change to `tox.ini` to rename a deprecated keyword ([details](https://tox.readthedocs.io/en/latest/config.html#conf-allowlist_externals))",
